# FocusTrack – Phase 1 Walkthrough

## What Was Built

### Backend: `FocusTrack.Api` (.NET 10)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `Models/User.cs` | Entity: Id, Email, PasswordHash, CreatedAt |
| `Models/Session.cs` | Entity: Id, UserId, AppName, WindowTitle, StartTime, EndTime, IsBrowser |
| `Data/FocusDbContext.cs` | EF Core DbContext with unique email index and timestamp indexes |
| `DTOs/RegisterDto.cs` | Input DTO with `[Required]` + `[EmailAddress]` annotations |
| `DTOs/LoginDto.cs` | Input DTO |
| `DTOs/AuthResponseDto.cs` | Output: Token, ExpiresAt, Email |
| `Services/AuthService.cs` | RegisterAsync + LoginAsync with BCrypt hashing, ILogger |
| `Controllers/AuthController.cs` | POST /api/auth/register, POST /api/auth/login |
| `Controllers/TestController.cs` | GET /api/test/protected — `[Authorize]` acceptance endpoint |
| `Middleware/GlobalExceptionHandlerMiddleware.cs` | Catches all unhandled exceptions, returns `{error, statusCode}` |
| `Program.cs` | Full pipeline: DbContext, JWT Bearer, CORS, OpenAPI, EnsureCreated |
| `appsettings.Development.json` | SQLite connection, JWT config, CORS allowed origins |

**Key design decisions:**
- JWT key read from `Jwt:Key` config — never hardcoded
- `db.Database.EnsureCreated()` on startup → SQLite DB auto-created at `focustrack.db`
- Native .NET 10 `AddOpenApi()` used (avoids Swashbuckle version conflicts)
- `FocusTrackCors` policy allows `http://localhost:4200`

