## Running the App

### 1. Start the API
```powershell
cd "e:\Learning Projects\AntiGravityTest1\FocusTrack.Api"
dotnet run
# API available at https://localhost:5001 (or http://localhost:5000)
# OpenAPI spec: https://localhost:5001/openapi/v1.json
```

### 2. Start the Angular UI
```powershell
cd "e:\Learning Projects\AntiGravityTest1\focus-track-ui"
ng serve
# UI available at http://localhost:4200
```

### 3. Acceptance Criteria Test
1. Navigate to `http://localhost:4200/register` → fill email + password → submit
2. Navigate to `http://localhost:4200/login` → log in → JWT stored in localStorage
3. Call `GET http://localhost:5000/api/test/protected` with `Authorization: Bearer <token>` → `200 OK`

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `Jwt:Key` in `appsettings.Development.json` is a dev placeholder. Before committing or sharing, move it to **user secrets**: `dotnet user-secrets set "Jwt:Key" "your-strong-32-char-secret"`

> [!NOTE]
> The `focus-track-ui` in `AuthService` has the API base URL hardcoded to `http://localhost:5000`. This should be moved to `environment.ts` in a later phase.
